Hillary Rodham Clinton says she has 'moved on' from the Monica Lewinsky scandal and told everyone else to do the same.

The former Secretary of State also revealed she did not read an essay Ms Lewinsky wrote for last month's Vanity Fair magazine that focuses on the scandal that dominated Bill Clinton's second term as president.

In an interview for this week's People magazine, Mrs Clinton said: 'I think everybody needs to look to the future,' referring to Ms Lewinsky.

