'But part of what I've been thinking about, is everything I'm interested in and everything I enjoy doing - and with the extra added joy of "I'm about to become a grandmother," I want to live in the moment.'

At the same time, however, she added: 'I am concerned about what I see happening in the country and in the world. Through the next months, I will think more about what role I can or, in my mind, should play.'

The comments come after her former boss - President Barack Obama - said he thinks she would be a 'very effective' president if she decides to run.

The President praised his former Secretary of State during an interview for Live with Kelly and Michael at the White House that aired last Friday.

'Hillary and I, we're buddies,' he said in the interview.

